title.en: Smart Tourism Ontology and Touristic recomendations

author: Raúl Ríos Redondo and José María Aguirre Carbonero

description.en: This is a Ontology provide terms related with tourist and recomendatios including cities, restaurants, events, touristic attactions and transportations.

comments.en: It corresponds to the PEC2 of the subject “Knowledge Representation”.

creator.value: Raúl Ríos Redondo and José María Aguirre Carbonero

contributor.value: Raúl Ríos Redondo and José María Aguirre Carbonero

isDefinedBy.value: José María Aguirre Carbonero &   Raúl Ríos Redondo

abstract.value:
Scope:
The ontology will focus solely on information related to tourist services offered by certain cities, including information about hotels, events, transportation, restaurants, and tourist attractions.

Goals:
The objective is for this ontology to be used to develop an application that provides information about relevant tourist services. This information can be utilized by private users seeking tourist information about a specific city, as well as by other applications, such as those used by travel agencies for planning organized trips.
